But if, notwithstanding the above related, so evident a Right in the Crown to confine the Boundaries of New-Jersey, on Delaware, to the Head of Delaware BAY, it should still be supposed, that the Duke had a Right to extend his Grant to the Proprietors of New-Jersey up Delaware RIVER; thus much however is undoubtedly certain, that they cannot go beyond the Words of their Grant; which, as your Memorialists 
